nd%20this%20is%20Kapil%20Sibal%20in%20his%20tweet%20very%20famously%20said%2C%20I%E2%80%99m%20quoting%20his%20tweet%2C%20he%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20Court%E2%80%99s%20verdict%20had%20little%20to%20do%20with%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20own%20understanding%20of%20Article%20370.%20The%20government%E2%80%99s%20understanding%20hinged%20upon%20a%20reinterpretation%20of%20the%20constituent%20assembly.%E2%80%9D%20The%20Court%E2%80%99s%20verdict%20didn%E2%80%99t%20hinge%20upon%20that%20at%20all%3B%20it%20found%20the%20reinterpretation%20of%20malafide%20and%20ultra%20vires.%20They%20said%20the%20route%20is%20371.%20Yeah%2C%20so%20in%20other%20words%2C%20they%20suggested%20to%20the%20government%20what%20the%20government%20could%20do%20even%20though%20the%20government%20hadn%E2%80%99t%20done%20it.%20And%20then%20presumed%20that%20if%20they%20had%20done%20it%2C%20it%20would%20be%20okay%2C%20therefore%20what%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20done%20is%20okay.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EML%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Yes%2C%20I%E2%80%99ll%20put%20it%20slightly%20differently.%20The%20case%20of%20the%20government%20was%20dependent%20upon%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20becoming%20the%20Legislative%20Assembly.%20Gee%2C%20that%20did%20not%20happen.%20Now%20if%20that%20does%20not%20happen%2C%20then%20the%20case%20falls%20to%20the%20ground.%20What%20the%20government%20also%20seems%20to%20have%20done%20or%20what%20the%20court%20seems%20to%20have%20done%2C%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20know%20if%20the%20government%20argued%20that%2C%20they%20said%20that%20the%20powers%20of%20the%20State%20Assembly%20are%20with%20the%20governor.%20The%20powers%20of%20the%20governor%20are%20with%20the%20president.%20The%20president%20says%2C%20or%20the%20Parliament%20says%2C%20and%20the%20President%20says%20that%2C%20all%20right%2C%20you%20delete%20Article%20370.%20So%20we%20delete%20Article%20370.%20That%E2%80%99s%20what%20the%20court%20says.%20Now%20I%E2%80%99m%20not%20sure%20whether%20that%20was%20argued%20because%20it%20could%20not%20have%20been%20argued.%20I%20would%20put%20it%20slightly%20differently.%20I%20would%20say%20that%20it%20could%20not%20have%20been%20argued%20because%20the%20case%20hinged%20upon%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20becoming%20the%20Legislative%20Assembly.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EKT%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20That%E2%80%99s%20right.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EML%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20There%20was%2C%20as%20far%20as%20I%20know%2C%20like%20I%20said%20it%E2%80%99s%20such%20a%20complicated%20judgment%20as%20far%20as%20I%20know%2C%20and%20the%20alternative%20argument%20was%20not%20advanced.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EKT%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20And%20yet%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20behaved%20as%20if%20it%20was.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EML%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Yes%2C%20yes.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EKT%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20And%20this%20is%20what%20I%20mean%20when%20I%20say%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20effectively%20put%20words%20in%20the%20mouths%20of%20the%20government%20because%20what%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20claims%20is%20the%20route%20you%20could%20do%20it%20by%20is%20not%20the%20route%20the%20government%20chose%20to%20do%20it%20by.%20Yeah%2C%20and%20the%20route%20the%20government%20chose%20to%20do%20it%20by%20reinterpreting%20Constituent%20Assembly%20to%20mean%20Legislative%20Assembly%20they%20struck%20down.%20Yeah%2C%20so%20in%20effect%20what%20they%E2%80%99re%20saying%20to%20the%20government%20is%20what%20you%20did%2C%20you%20did%20the%20wrong%20way%20and%20we%20ought%20really%20to%20be%20striking%20it%20down%2C%20but%20we%20won%E2%80%99t%20because%20there%E2%80%99s%20another%20way%20of%20doing%20it%20which%20you%20didn%E2%80%99t%20choose%20but%20had%20you%20chosen%20it%20would%20have%20been%20correct.%20Yeah%2C%20and%20we%E2%80%99ll%20give%20you%20the%20benefit%20of%20the%20doubt.%20Yeah%2C%20and%20that%E2%80%99s%20convoluted%20logic%20to%20me.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EML%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Yes%2C%20it%20is.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EKT%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20And%20it%20seems%20to%20me%20that%20not%20only%20is%20it%20convoluted%2C%20but%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20sort%20of%20tied%20itself%20in%20because%20instead%20of%20adjudicating%20what%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20done%2C%20they%E2%80%99re%20virtually%20advocating%20to%20the%20government%20what%20it%20should%20have%20done.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EML%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Yeah%2C%20they%E2%80%99ve%20not%20put%20these%20words%20crudely%20is%20that%2C%20yeah%2C%20but%20I%20mean%20they%20said%20this%2C%20this%20is%20how%20it%20is.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EKT%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20So%20as%20a%20former%20very%20highly%20regarded%20judge%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20you%E2%80%99re%20rather%20unhappy%20with%20the%20way%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20handled%20this%20issue%20of%20abrogation.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EML%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Yes%2C%20yes%2C%20I%20am%20unhappy%20because%20I%E2%80%99m%20not%20sure%20how%20they%E2%80%99ve%20come%20to%20certain%20conclusions%20and%20certain%20conclusions%20they%20have%2C%20like%20this%20constitution%20of%20India%20can%20be%20applied%20in%20full%20state%2C%20how%20have%20they%20come%20to%20that%20conclusion%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EKT%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20They%20sort%20of%20asserted%20it%2C%20yeah%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20like%20an%20assertion.%20They%E2%80%99ve%20also%20come%20to%20the%20conclusion%2C%20I%20think%2C%20like%20in%20paragraph%20400%20or%20something%20or%20420%20or%20something%20that%20Article%20370%20could%20be%20abrogated.%20How%20did%20they%20come%20to%20that%20conclusion%3F%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EAgain%2C%20they%E2%80%99ve%20asserted%20it.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2