%20Charles%20making%20a%20casual%20reference%20to%20his%20well-known%20%26quot%3Bsausage%20fingers.%26quot%3B%20In%20the%20upcoming%20behind-the-scenes%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fuk-67763074%5C%22%3EBBC%20documentary%2C%20'Charles%20III%3A%20The%20Coronation%20Year'%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Prince%20William%20is%20seen%20rehearsing%20for%20the%20event%20by%20using%20his%20hands%20to%20close%20a%20small%20clasp%20holding%20a%20robe%20around%20his%20father.%20In%20the%20footage%2C%20the%20Prince%20of%20Wales%20jokingly%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BOn%20the%20day%2C%20that's%20not%20going%20to%20go%20in.%26quot%3B%20To%20which%2C%20King%20Charles%20replied%2C%20%26quot%3BNo%2C%20you%20haven't%20got%20sausage%20fingers%20like%20mine.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20this%20is%20not%20the%20first%20time%20that%20King%20Charles%20has%20discussed%20his%20fingers.%20According%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.independent.co.uk%2Flife-style%2Froyal-family%2Fnews%2Fking-charles-sausage-fingers-queen-b2468453.html%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EIndependent%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20after%20Prince%20William%20was%20born%2C%20King%20Charles%20supposedly%20wrote%20to%20a%20friend%20and%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20can't%20tell%20you%20how%20excited%20and%20proud%20I%20am.%20He%20really%20does%20look%20surprisingly%20appetising%20and%20has%20sausage%20fingers%20just%20like%20mine.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20he%20was%20the%20Prince%20of%20Wales%2C%20King%20Charles%20would%20occasionally%20make%20fun%20of%20his%20fingers%2C%20which%20he%20called%20%26quot%3Bsausage%20fingers%26quot%3B.%20Whenever%20they%20are%20featured%20prominently%20in%20a%20photo%2C%20they%20spark%20a%20lot%20of%20attention%20on%20the%20internet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20documentary%20takes%20viewers%20behind%20the%20scenes%20as%20everything%20is%20put%20together%20for%20the%20big%20day%2C%20including%20the%20removal%20of%20the%20royal%20jewels%2C%20the%20work%20of%20the%20Royal%20School%20of%20Needlework%2C%20and%20the%20arrival%20of%20the%20anointing%20oil%20used%20by%20the%20King%20and%20Queen%20from%20the%20Holy%20Land.%20It%20will%20air%20on%20BBC%20One%20and%20iPlayer%20on%20December%2026%20at%2018%3A50%20GMT.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20May%206%2C%20King%20Charles%20became%20the%2040th%20British%20monarch%20to%20be%20crowned%20at%20Westminster%20Abbey%20in%20London.%20Around%202%2C300%20guests%2C%20including%20foreign%20leaders%20and%20global%20royalty%2C%20attended%20the%20event%2C%20which%20was%20the%20religious%20confirmation%20of%20Charles's%20accession%20following%20the%20death%20of%20Queen%20Elizabeth%20II%20in%20September%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20come%20not%20to%20be%20served%2C%20but%20to%20serve%2C%26quot%3B%20King%20Charles%20said%20in%20his%20first%20prayer%20after%20reaching%20the%20Abbey.%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20here%20to%20crown%20a%20King%2C%20and%20we%20crown%20a%20King%20to%20serve%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Archbishop%20opened%20his%20sermon%20with.%26quot%3BThe%20King%20of%20Kings%2C%20Jesus%20Christ%2C%20was%20anointed%20not%20to%20be%20served%2C%20but%20to%20serve.%20He%20creates%20the%20unchangeable%20law%20that%20with%20the%20privilege%20of%20power%20comes%20the%20duty%20to%20serve%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPrince%20William%20also%20pledged%20loyalty%20to%20King%20Charles.%20Prince%20Harry%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20arrived%20from%20the%20United%20States%20on%20a%20commercial%20flight%2C%20and%20was%20seen%20entering%20the%20church%20with%20his%20cousins%20Princess%20Eugenie%20and%20Princess%20Beatrice.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20coronation%20was%20the%20first%20since%201953%20and%20the%20first%20of%20a%20king%20since%201937.%20It%20was%20only%20the%20second%20to%20be%20televised%20and%20the%20first%20in%20colour%20and%20streamed%20online.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703386380000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-05%2Fqho9njq_king