s%20had%20wanted%20to%20take%20over%20as%20company%20president%2C%20Markkula%20feared%20that%20he%20still%20lacked%20the%20experience%20and%20temperament%20to%20lead%20Apple.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFollowing%20a%20string%20of%20product%20flops%2C%20Sculley%20was%20replaced%20in%201993%20at%20the%20direction%20of%20the%20board%20of%20directors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EMichael%20Spindler%20(1993-1996)%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMichael%20Spindler%20was%20initially%20recruited%20to%20Apple%20by%20Mike%20Makkula%20with%20the%20goal%20of%20helping%20its%20European%20presence.%20Prior%20to%20becoming%20Apple%20CEO%2C%20he%20was%20the%20company's%20Chief%20Operating%20Officer.%20Under%20his%20tenure%2C%20Apple%20went%20through%20a%20major%20restructuring%20and%20launched%20a%20mixed%20portfolio%20of%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223648%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Michael%20Spindler%20stands%20in%20front%20of%20computer%20monitors%20and%20keyboards%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6582c831a79e5746976b6834%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222395%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMichael%20Spindler.%3Cp%3EWilliam%20Stevens%2FGamma-Rapho%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESpindler%20was%20at%20the%20helm%20for%20the%20successful%20launch%20of%20Apple's%20PowerPC%20product%20line.%20In%201994%20he%20led%20Apple%20into%20a%20partnership%20with%20IBM%20and%20Motorola%2C%20forming%20the%20AIM%20alliance%20with%20the%20goal%20of%20achieving%20a%20dominant%20position%20as%20the%20primary%20computer%20operating%20system%2C%20a%20title%20still%20held%20by%20Microsoft.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFollowing%20the%20success%20of%20the%20alliance%2C%20Apple%20allowed%20Motorola%20and%20others%20to%20make%20clones%20of%20the%20Macintosh%3B%20two%20years%20later%2C%2075%20clones%20had%20been%20made.%20This%20ultimately%20concerned%20Apple%20that%20it%20could%20jeopardize%20sales%20of%20its%20own%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EGilbert%20Fra