0We%20all%20start%20there.%20As%20soon%20as%20I%20fell%20in%20love%20with%20the%20game%20and%20started%20studying%20it%20on%20my%20own%2C%20I%20realized%20I%20was%20not%20unlucky%20%E2%80%94%20I%20was%20just%20making%20mathematically%20incorrect%20decisions.%20To%20think%20like%20a%20poker%20player%2C%20you%20have%20to%20change%20how%20you%20think%20about%20the%20game%20and%20start%20to%20see%20those%20patterns%2C%20and%20that%20only%20comes%20with%20reps.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20studied%20philosophy%20and%20mathematics%20at%20Wake%20Forest%20University.%20I%20fell%20in%20love%20with%20how%20philosophy%20got%20me%20to%20think%20about%20the%20world%2C%20and%20I%20fell%20in%20love%20with%20how%20math%20helped%20me%20analyze%20it.%20That's%20basically%20what%20you're%20doing%20in%20poker.%20You're%20thinking%20about%20the%20situations%20analytically%20and%20critically.%20You%20can%20use%20your%20people%20skills%20and%20how%20you%20think%20others%20might%20perceive%20the%20world%2C%20or%20in%20this%20case%2C%20the%20table%2C%20and%20then%20you%20can%20use%20mathematical%20skills%20to%20back%20your%20decisions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20love%20the%20competitive%20nature%20of%20playing%20with%20other%20people%2C%20and%20if%20you%20can%20get%20good%20at%20something%20and%20make%20money%20doing%20it%2C%20that%20is%20something%20that%20piques%20my%20interest.%20The%20things%20that%20you'll%20gain%20by%20learning%20poker%20and%20understanding%20the%20game%20will%20be%20the%20same%20no%20matter%20where%20you%20go%20with%20it.%20The%20experiences%20that%20I%20was%20having%20at%20the%20%2420%20tables%2C%20I'm%20still%20having%20in%20the%20%2410%2C000%20events.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20known%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsue-wagner-muffy-macmillan-entrepreneurship-gender-gap-funding-wendy-daimond-2023-12%23jenny-just-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJenny%20Just%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.co