%E2%80%9C%E2%80%A6I%20would%20like%20to%20state%20that%20as%20a%20committed%20opposition%2C%20we%20firmly%20believe%20in%20fostering%20dialogue%20and%20discussion%2C%20which%20are%20fundamental%20pillars%20of%20any%20parliamentary%20democracy%2C%E2%80%9D%20Kharge%20said%20in%20the%20letter.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CI%20would%20like%20to%20bring%20to%20your%20attention%20that%20multiple%20notices%20were%20submitted%20under%20the%20relevant%20rules%20of%20the%20Rules%20and%20Procedure%20of%20the%20Council%20of%20States%20(Rajya%20Sabha)%20to%20address%20the%20pressing%20issue%20of%20the%20breach%20of%20Parliament%20security.%20The%20Opposition%20parties%20were%20prepared%20to%20engage%20in%20a%20meaningful%20discussion%20on%20the%20matter.%20Regrettably%2C%20these%20notices%20were%20neither%20admitted%2C%20nor%20was%20I%2C%20as%20the%20Leader%20of%20the%20Opposition%20parties%2C%20permitted%20to%20speak%20on%20the%20floor%20of%20the%20House%20even%20for%20a%20minute%20or%20two%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKharge%E2%80%99s%20letter%20came%20a%20day%20after%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20chairman%20wrote%20to%20him%20over%20disruptions%20and%20acrimony%20in%20the%20parliament.%20Dhankar%20had%20alleged%20that%20Kharge%20had%20refused%20to%20meet%20him%20to%20resolve%20the%20political%20stalemate%20in%20the%20House.%20He%20said%20that%20the%20opposition%20MPs%20by%20%E2%80%9Cmaking%20a%20demand%20to%20the%20Chair%E2%80%9D%20that%20could%20not%20be%20acceded%20was%20a%20way%20to%20render%20the%20House%20dysfunctional%2C%20and%20was%20%E2%80%9Cunfortunate%20and%20against%20the%20public%20interest.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKharge%E2%80%99s%20letter%20also%20coincided%20with%20Shah%E2%80%99s%20statement%20at%20an%20event%20on%20Thursday.%20%E2%80%9CAs%20a%20legislator%2C%20I%20was%20piloting%20the%20Bill%20in%20Parliament.%20I%20wanted%20the%20opposition%20to%20present%20its%20views%20and%20suggestions%20on%20the%20Bills.%20But%2C%20unfortunately%2C%20they%20decided%20to%20boycott%20the%20discussion%20by%20making%20excuses%2C%E2%80%9D%20Shah%20said.%20%3Cspan%3EThe%20home%20minister%20also%20said%20when%20the%20new%20criminal%20justice%20bills%20were%20being%20discussed%2C%20the%20%E2%80%9Copposition%20was%20busy%20mimicking%20the%20vice-president%20outside%20the%20House.%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%9CThere%20cannot%20be%20a%20more%20condemnable%20action%20than%20this%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20Shah%20didn%E2%80%99t%20make%20it%20clear%20that%20a%20majority%20of%20the%20opposition%20MPs%20had%20already%20been%20suspended%20when%20the%20criminal%20justice%20bills%20were%20tabled%2C%20which%20had%20made%20it%20impossible%20for%20most%20opposition%20MPs%20to%20participate%20in%20the%20discussions.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMany%20critics%20have%20already%20pointed%20out%20that%20important%20Bills%20like%20the%20new%20criminal%20justice%20bills%20and%20the%20Telecommunications%20Bill%202023%20were%20passed%20without%20any%20discussions%20in%20parliament.%20The%20Union%20government%E2%80%99s%20reluctance%20to%20issue%20an%20official%20statement%20on%20the%20security%20breach%2C%20even%20as%20both%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20and%20home%20minister%20have%20been%20speaking%20about%20the%20episode%20on%20public%20platforms%2C%20has%20also%20been%20questioned%20by%20many%20observers.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAmidst%20mass%20suspensions%20of%20opposition%20MPs%2C%20the%20opposition%20MPs%20have%20been%20demanding%20that%20Shah%20should%20make%20an%20official%20statement%20in%20the%20parliament%20about%20the%20security%20breach.%20Until%20now%2C%20146%20MPs%20have%20already%20been%20suspended%20from%20both%20Houses%20after%20the%20BJP%2C%20which%20enjoys%20a%20brute%20majority%2C%20demanded%20their%20suspension.%20The%20last%20few%20sessions%20have%20been%20witness%20to%20the%20fact%20that%20none%20of%20the%20demands%20or%20requests%20put%20forward%20by%20the%20opposition%20parties%20was%20accommodated%20by%20the%20union%20government%20or%20the%20chairs%20of%20the%20Houses.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EKharge%20went%20on%20to%20say%20that%20the%20opposition%20parties%20merely%20wanted%20a%20discussion%20on%20the%20security%20breach%20but%20the%20requests%20were%20%E2%80%9Cunequivocally%20ignored%E2%80%9D%2C%20despite%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20matter%20%E2%80%9Cwas%20of%20grave%20concern%20to%20the%20Parliament%2C%20Parliamentarians%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cis%20also%20a%20significant%20national%20security%20issue.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CDespite%20these%20challenges%2C%20I%20want%20to%20reiterate%20my%20commitment%20to%20open%20discussion%20and%20dialogue%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20told%20Dhankar%2C%20while%20seeking%20an%20appointment%20with%20him%20to%20discuss%20these%20issues.%20Kharge%20said%20that%20he%20hoped%20that%20as%20the%20Chair%20of%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%2C%20he%20hoped%20that%20Dhankar%20would%20%E2%80%9Caccommodate%20the%20concerns%20of%20the%20opposition%20at%20all%20times.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20government%20will%20have%20its%20way%2C%20but%20the%20Opposition%20must%2C%20you%20will%20readily%20agree%2C%20have%20its%20say.%20I%20have%20no%20doubt%20that%20you%20will%20uphold%20this%20basic%20principle%20of%20parliamentary%20democracy%20in%20letter%20and%20spirit%2C%E2%80%9D%20Kharge%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703321664000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F08195802%2FFvdNgGTXgAAAOBm.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Foppositions-efforts-to-have-a-meaningful-discussion-in-parliament-were-ignored-kharge-to-dhankar%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Leader%20of%20the%20Opposition's%20letter%20to%20Rajya%20Sabha%20chai